Nov 15 2009 	Still great	This is our third or fourth time at this hotel. I have already reviewed it on tripadvisor twice. This review includes everything said in those other 2 reviews and the following:We were only able to book a deluxe room on such short notice. Everything was booked because of the Dubai Airshow 2009.We were honestly expecting the norm in terms of room and bathroom size. You know, the regular square/rectangle room with a bathroom usually at the entrance. The deluxe rooms are closer to suites than regular rooms in terms of size, decor and most importantly layout.There is a nice flat screen TV on the wall, mini bar and DVD player hidden in the cupboard/decor below the TV. Beautiful view of the Festival City Marina and Mall.Bathroom was also nice, especially with the natural light flowing in from the large window towards the tub. His and hers sink style.I have to add that customer service is top at this hotel. We had asked for a late checkout on the morning of the day we were supposed to checkout but that was not possible because of the event. A few hours later we got a call saying it was possible to extend checkout another 3 hours. We had not asked them to call us back if there was a chance of a late checkout. They must have noted it in the system and directly called us when they realized it was possible. Now thats great customer service. Other hotels should learn.Also notice the strawberries &amp; cream, fruit and carbonated Date drink complimentary as I mentioned it was a special anniversary for us.I should mention 2 things.First, the hotel has 2 main views, of the marina and the mall and of Dubai city. Both are great but the city is a little distant so its not a very immediate view of the skyline and the marina area (at time of writing) has a little construction going on so both are ok, depends on what you like.Second,I would urge you to opt for a club room (whether its a regular room or a suite) as the club lounge is just fantastic. Nice books/journals/magazines to skim while sipping on an espresso or fresh juice and snacks on the top floor.	
