Oct 23 2009 	Very pleasant with some glitches - but please avoid the hair salon at all costs!	This is a pleasant and convenient stopover for business travelers with a bit of free time. The location connected to a shopping mall with a lot of basic shops makes it easy to tick off a few errands, catch a movie, or grab an inexpensive bite to eat without the hassle of searching for a cab. The rooms are pleasant with an interesting modern-ish decor in neutral colors. I had a non-Creek view, but thought it was quite nice, especially at night when the lights were on in the city. Loved the big picture window in the bathroom by the tub. As with every Dubai hotel I've ever stayed in, I found that the service often had little errors - bathrobe not replaced by the cleaners, a promised return phone call from the salon/spa (when the line was busy as I was trying to book an appointment) never materialised, a room service order was delivered with different contents than those described on the menu. That being said, these problems were all quickly remedied with a pleasant smile, and if you're a reasonably good natured person they're not the sort of thing that will mar your stay. Even the best hotels make the occasional mistakes, I mention them here only because I experienced rather a lot of these little errors, and it made me wonder if the staff training and/or the service operation is fully up to the standard you would expect at the rates the hotel charges.I did not especially care for the pool. I visited it for a few hours on a Friday and found that it was fairly small, and a bit overrun by harassed nannies and their overindulged (and very very loud) Emirati charges. That being said, I did notice that the pool attendants were really kind to the children and quite good to them, even when they had to offer a few reprimands for the inevitable running around the deck sort of thing that all excited kids do when they're having fun at the pool. So it might be a nice afternoon for families traveling with children.A word about the beauty salon. It's actually a part of the spa, which I suppose for some people would be attractive because it's certainly a pleasant and glamorous space. But I actually found it annoying. I suppose if you're in vacation mode the very very relaxed pace of services would be enjoyable and might feel indulgent. But I was just trying to fit in a few grooming services on a day off during some extended business travel, and I found the pacing unbearable. The young women who gently and sloooooowly washed my hair, for example, was taking so long to comb it out that I finally just asked her to hand me the comb and did it myself. I was in urgent need of a cut and highlights and so took a chance on the services, a choice I absolutely would NOT recommend to anyone else. I was quite explicit in indicating that I wanted highlights and the shade I wanted, but the young man who was performing the services initially said &quot;I think I will do single color.&quot; I had to correct him, quite firmly, to ensure I got the process that I had booked. When he completed the color, I found to my horror that my hair was about 4 shades lighter than it ever has been, and certainly much lighter than I had requested. When I expressed that the results were not what I had requested, he responded that it &quot;wasn't that dark&quot; and that he liked it. I responded that it was indeed much much lighter than I had requested, and that while it was kind of him to say it looked nice, I was interested in pleasing my own tastes, not his. I told him he needed to correct it, and he tried to avoid doing it that evening. I politely insisted, and he did comply, in the end with good grace. But the whole ordeal took three hours, which would have been fine, I suppose, had the magazine selection been better. The cut itself was unremarkable, though a bit sloppy. I'll need to have it cleaned up when I eventually return home. The price for all of this was not inexpensive (about $150 more than I usually pay for full hair services), and so I have to say that I absolutely would NOT recommend the salon to new customers who don't think they'll have time to have errors corrected.	
