May 13 2009 	Wow!! Fantastic new hotel and lots to do	We stayed at the InterCon in Festival City for 3 days. Close to airport, 10 mins drive. 15 - 20 mins away from Deira and Bur Dubai, but taxi ride is cheap... about $10-20 if I remember right... nothing outrageous anyways. The hotel is brand spanking new. Excellent location, views, facilities, pool, gym, restaurants, bar. etc. ANd the bonus is that it is connected to an excellent mall (very expensive and designer outlets mainly) which is fabulous for window shopping, walking around, kids activities, free Venetian boatride in a long canal, superb restaurants that are reasonably priced. It is also connected to the adjoining Crowne Plaza hotel, which is also an excellent hotel with absolutely stunning rooms done in straight lines, zen, leather, wood, and veneer. Massive glass windows in rooms of both hotels from which the view of the harbour is fantastic. Ask for the room that faces the skyline across the Dubai Creek.Service is for the most part very very good. Make sure you go to a happy face at the front desk as a couple of people looked bored of their jobs, but just avoid those sloppy revengeful faces. 95% of the staff is very good. Crowne Plaza also has one of those rare Belgian beer bars. Superb beers, and fabulous dining experience on the outdoor patio overlooking the still waters, with gas lamp heating in the winter. Intercon has a superb bar also with nice outdoor seating venue. Only downside is that there are a couple of pay girls working the bar, but 3-4 every night. WHich is not too much of an irritance at all as it is very discreet and not as bad as Hyatt, Radisson etc other hotels located downtown. It is the Dubai phenomenon, so have to turn a blind eye to that as long as it is not too in your face. Other than that, excellent property, new, clean, well maintained, good service levels, and child friendly. Good for a family visit. Hotel restaurants are very expensive, so just walk for 5 mins to Festival City Mall and eat there. About 15 restaurants of all cuisine types, and another 15 fast food eateries plus 5 coffee houses. IKEA and TOys R Us have good shopping deals sometimes, so enjoy. Make sure you shop on the internet for a good deal. You should be able to get rooms here for $100 - $150 per night for double room as of April 2009, so don't pay much more at either InterCon or Crowne Plaza Festival City. Then its excellent value. Enjoy...	
