Feb 24 2009 	Good Business Hotel not so good for Leisure	Situated on the airport side of the Creek, on a clear day the hotel has great views over the towers &amp; building projects of Dubai, however it is some distance from the hub of Dubai, the main malls and the beaches. There's a small mall adjacent which meets basic needs and offers some lower cost dining options, but otherwise most of Dubai's attractions are a drive or taxi-ride away. The hotel is nicely appointed and met most of my husband's business needs' however as a leisure visitor, I thought the pool area was fairly dull and the choice of restaurants a bit small. Breakfast in Anise was a nightmare. Lots of staff running around ineffectually - but then that is Dubai. Very poor value for money. Bistro Madeleine however was lovely, excellent food, charming staff. All in all, a good place for the business man, but there is more luxury to be had in Dubai for the same money, especially if you want a bit of R &amp; R	
